  text: What’s wrong is this line:

```vb
c.Value = ("C2") = Left(ws.Range("C2"), Len(ws.Range("C2")) - 3)
```

`("C2") = Left(...)` is a comparison, not an assignment to the cell text you want.  
So VBA evaluates that expression as `True` or `False`, then writes the boolean result into every cell.

You also keep referring to `ws.Range("C2")` inside the loop, so even if it worked, it would only use cell `C2` repeatedly instead of each cell `c`.

The VBA should be:

```vb
